Install:
via CDN - You can't customise

* install postcss phpstorm plugin
* install
* run TW init command
* add TW build scripts
*  run npm build - to build as per "scripts" command
* support html in TW config file
* 'Utility first (which is what TW is) means you apply styles by adding classes to the HTML.
* using the 'media' option to switch dark mode in tailwind.config.js uses the OS color mode.
* using the 'class' option uses whatever custom classes you have created.